<task id="070" project="sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair">
  <metadata>
    <title>P23.L1 — LOW-tier Api/* batch 1 (triage repair vs archive, ~22 files)</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>3-5 hours</estimated-effort>
    <assigned>AI agent</assigned>
    <tags>phase-2-3, low-tier, p23-l, bff-api, testing, triage</tags>
    <parallel-group>23-L</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Named Api/* test files (1st quarter of ~88) are disjoint from sibling batches 071, 072, 073</parallel-reason>
    <rigor>STANDARD</rigor>
    <repair-not-rewrite>true</repair-not-rewrite>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Triage and repair OR archive the LOW-tier Api/* tests — batch 1 of 4 (~22 files in
    `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Api/*.cs`, 1st quarter alphabetically of the ~88-file LOW-tier
    set per design.md §3.3). Per design.md §3.3 LOW-tier rationale: most tests duplicate synthetic
    smoke coverage; per-file judgment required — repair if unique response-shape contract,
    archive if duplicate of synthetic smoke.

    Per FR-20 P23.L START GATE: this batch MUST NOT start until P23.H (tasks 040-046) AND P23.M
    (tasks 050-056) are each ≥50% complete. Verify upstream progress before starting.

    For each test file:
    1. Determine: is this test a unique response-shape contract test (KEEP, repair), OR is it
       a route-registration / auth-check / smoke-style test duplicated by synthetic smoke (ARCHIVE)?
    2. If KEEP: repair assertions; apply `[Trait("status", "repaired")]`; verify Pass
    3. If ARCHIVE: rename file to `&lt;OldName&gt;.cs.archived-2026-MM-DD` per §6.5; add entry to
       `ledgers/archive-ledger.md` with justification (cite synthetic-smoke equivalence)

    ESCALATION TRIGGER: If archive count in this batch exceeds 10 files → ESCALATE per NFR-04
    BEFORE proceeding. File owner-approval request in `escalations/archive-approval-T-070.md`.

    Per project CLAUDE.md NFR-02 + design.md §4.1: this is repair, NOT rewrite. If ANY repaired
    file's diff would exceed 50% line replacement, HALT and file
    `projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/escalations/rewrite-request-T-070-{FileName}.md`
    per §4.8 escalation procedure. Do NOT proceed without owner approval.

    NO production code changes (NFR-01). NO silent deletion — archive via rename only (NFR-06).
    Per §6.2, every touched test ends in `repaired`, `real-bug-pending-fix`, `flaky-quarantined`,
    OR is archived. `Failed` is FORBIDDEN at close.
  </prompt>

  <role>Senior .NET test repair specialist with API endpoint testing + smoke-test coverage judgment.</role>

  <goal>
    ~22 Api/* test files triaged. Repaired files Pass. Archived files renamed with archive-ledger
    entries. Zero Failed.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="spec">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="design">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/design.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="baseline">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/baseline/test-baseline-2026-MM-DD.trx</file>
    <file purpose="archive-ledger">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/ledgers/archive-ledger.md</file>
    <file purpose="archive-precedent">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/JobProcessorTests.cs.archived-2025-10-14</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="NFR-01">MUST NOT modify production code in `src/`, `power-platform/`, `infra/`, `scripts/`</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-02">MUST NOT replace &gt;50% of any file without §4.8 escalation</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-04">Archive count &gt;10 in this batch triggers owner escalation</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-06">MUST NOT silently delete tests; archive via rename to `*.cs.archived-2026-MM-DD`</constraint>
    <constraint source="§6.2">Every touched test gets a §6.2 final end-state (or archived)</constraint>
    <constraint source="§4.5">MUST NOT touch `CustomWebAppFactory.cs`</constraint>
    <constraint source="FR-19">All LOW-tier tests must end in §6.2 final end-state</constraint>
    <constraint source="FR-20">Start gate: P23.H and P23.M each ≥50% complete</constraint>
    <constraint source="batch-partition">Batch 1 covers 1st quarter of Api/* files alphabetically; respect partition</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/design.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/api.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per design.md §3.3 LOW-tier (~88 files) is mostly endpoint route-registration / auth-check /
      status-code tests. Most are duplicates of synthetic smoke coverage. Triage default: archive
      if duplicate, KEEP if response-shape contract. NFR-04 enforces &gt;10-archives-per-batch escalation.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="040" status="not-started">P23.H1 Workspace scoring</dependency>
      <dependency task="041" status="not-started">P23.H2 Scorecard</dependency>
      <dependency task="042" status="not-started">P23.H3 Finance signals</dependency>
      <dependency task="043" status="not-started">P23.H4 Email association</dependency>
      <dependency task="044" status="not-started">P23.H5 Ai/Safety</dependency>
      <dependency task="045" status="not-started">P23.H6 Filters + Json</dependency>
      <dependency task="046" status="not-started">P23.H7 Resilience (≥50% of P23.H complete required)</dependency>
      <dependency task="050" status="not-started">P23.M1 Ai/Chat batch 1</dependency>
      <dependency task="051" status="not-started">P23.M2 Ai/Chat batch 2</dependency>
      <dependency task="052" status="not-started">P23.M3 Ai/Chat batch 3</dependency>
      <dependency task="053" status="not-started">P23.M4 Ai/Capabilities (≥50% of P23.M complete required)</dependency>
    </dependencies>
  </context>

  <relevant-files>
    <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Api/&lt;first quarter of files alphabetically, excluding subdirectories already covered&gt;</file>
  </relevant-files>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Verify FR-20 start gate: confirm ≥50% of tasks 040-046 (P23.H) AND ≥50% of tasks 050-056 (P23.M) are status=completed in TASK-INDEX.md. If not, HALT and report.</step>
    <step order="2">List all `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Api/*.cs` files (excluding subdirectories already covered by other tasks). Sort alphabetically. Take first quarter (~22 files) → this is batch 1.</step>
    <step order="3">From Phase 0 baseline TRX, identify failing tests within this batch.</step>
    <step order="4">For each file: determine REPAIR vs ARCHIVE via per-test judgment. Read the test; does it assert a unique response shape (KEEP), or does it duplicate route-registration / status-code checking already in synthetic smoke (ARCHIVE)?</step>
    <step order="5">Track archive count as you go. If approaching 10 → STOP triaging more for archive; file `escalations/archive-approval-T-070.md` per NFR-04 BEFORE proceeding past 10.</step>
    <step order="6">For REPAIR cases: compute pre-edit line count; if &gt;50% replacement → escalate per §4.8. Otherwise apply minimal edits; mark `[Trait("status", "repaired")]`.</step>
    <step order="7">For ARCHIVE cases: rename file to `&lt;OldName&gt;.cs.archived-2026-MM-DD`; add entry to `ledgers/archive-ledger.md` with file path, justification (cite synthetic-smoke equivalence path), and date.</step>
    <step order="8">After each file: `dotnet test --filter "FullyQualifiedName~Api"` (intersected with batch) verify outcome.</step>
    <step order="9">Update `current-task.md` with disposition table (file | REPAIR/ARCHIVE | reason).</step>
    <step order="10">Verify `git status` shows NO modifications under `src/`, `power-platform/`, `infra/`, `scripts/`.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="dotnet">test</tool>
    <tool name="git">status + mv (for archive rename)</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">~22 Api/* test files (repaired or archived)</output>
    <output type="docs">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/ledgers/archive-ledger.md (entries for any archived files)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">All batch-1 LOW-tier tests Pass, Skip-with-reason, or are archived; zero Failed</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">FR-20 start gate verified before work began (50% P23.H + 50% P23.M complete)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Per-file repair diff &lt;50% line replacement (NFR-02); archived files renamed per §6.5</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Archive count ≤10 in this batch, OR `escalations/archive-approval-T-070.md` exists with owner approval (NFR-04)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Every touched test has a §6.2 final end-state trait OR is archived with ledger entry</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`git status` shows zero changes under `src/`, `power-platform/`, `infra/`, `scripts/`</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No overlap with batches 071, 072, 073 files</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    <scope-extension date="2026-05-31">
      Wave 1 baseline reconciliation (task 008) — MATERIAL EXPANSION. This batch (first quarter
      of Api/*.cs alphabetically) absorbs Api/Ai/* + Api/Agent/* clusters: 97 failures across
      14 classes. Specifically:
        - Api/Ai/*: PlaybookRunEndpoints (20), StandaloneChatContextEndpoints (18),
          HandlerEndpoints (11), AnalysisChatContextEndpoints (10), NodeEndpoints (10),
          ModelEndpoints (8), ChatSessionPlanEndpoint (5), ChatRefineEndpoint (4),
          DailyBriefingEndpoints (2), R2SseEventEmitter (1)
        - Api/Agent/*: AgentConversation (3), HandoffUrlBuilder (3), AgentConfiguration (1)
      Several classes show 100% failure rate (PlaybookRun, StandaloneChatContext, Handler,
      Node, Model, ChatSessionPlan, ChatRefine, DailyBriefing) — suggests endpoint-wide
      regression (auth/route/factory startup), likely one root cause per cluster.
      Investigate root cause BEFORE per-test edits.

      Effort impact: significantly higher than original STANDARD-rigor estimate. Consider
      splitting batch 1 into 1a (Api/Ai/* — 10 classes) and 1b (Api/Agent/* — 3 classes)
      with 1a as its own wave-2.5 sub-task. Owner may revise wave plan.
      See `notes/handoffs/phase23-scope-delta-2026-05-31.md`.
    </scope-extension>
  </notes>
</task>
